'''{{Colour|red|Warning}}:''' [[Vet'ion]] resides in a [[multi-way]] area in moderately high-level [[Wilderness]]. Completion of the medium [[Wilderness Diary]] is required to fight Vet'ion.

You may be attacked at any time during the fight, and death is all but guaranteed in any deep wilderness [[multicombat area]]. '''Do not''' bring any items that you are not willing to lose. Untradeable items like the [[Dragon defender]] and [[Salve amulet (e)]] are '''permanently''' lost if not protected beyond level 20 Wilderness.

==Transportation==
[[Vet'ion]] resides in [[Vet'ion's Rest]], the entrance of which is located just north of the [[Bone Yard]]. There is a small building where he originally roamed before his rework where the player may drop into his chambers, requiring a fee of 50,000 coins to enter which can be taken from the bank. This fee decreases by 10,000 for every kill for the player who deals the most damage. The fee is not required again on subsequent trips unless killed by another player.

To get there quickly, you can:

*Teleport to the level 40 [[Revenant Caves]] entrance with a [[Revenant cave teleport]], then run south-east.
*Teleport to [[Carralanger teleport|Carralanger]] with a [[Carrallanger teleport (tablet)|tablet]] or your PoH portal, then run north-east.
*Teleport to [[Annakarl]] with a [[Annakarl teleport (tablet)|tablet]] or your PoH portal, then run south-west.
*Teleport to the [[Wilderness Obelisk]] at level 35 wildy from outside [[Ferox Enclave]] or your PoH, then run east.
*Teleport to the [[Corporeal Beast's Lair]] with a [[Games necklace]] or your PoH, then exit the cave and run north.
*Teleport to the [[Black chinchompa (Hunter)|black chinchompa]] hunting ground with level 99 [[Hunter]] and a [[hunter cape]], then run east. NOTE: as [[Vet'ion's Rest]] lies beyond level 20 Wilderness, you will LOSE your cape on death.
*Ride a [[waka canoe]] up to the Wilderness pond from any [[canoe]] station with 57 [[Woodcutting]] and any type of [[axe]], then run east.

